message.content:
I need to calculate the Gross Profit Margin based on the income statement. The Gross Profit Margin is calculated as (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%.

From the income statement:
- Gross Profit = $6,476,677.56
- Total Revenue = $22,876,677.56

Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = ($6,476,677.56 / $22,876,677.56) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 0.2831 × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 28.31%

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '28.31%'}}
```
